DGCM Exporter Datacenter GPU Manager Exporter

Great! Tu ab DCGM Exporter ke baare mein poochh raha hai â€” ye GPU workloads ke monitoring ke liye important 
hota hai, especially jab AWS ParallelCluster ya Kubernetes me NVIDIA GPU based nodes use kar rahe ho.
Ye NVIDIA ka tool hai jo tere cluster ke GPU metrics ko Prometheus-compatible format me export karta hai.

Yaani:

GPU ka health
Utilization
Temperature
Memory usage
Power usage
â†’ ye sab metrics Prometheus ko deta hai.



ğŸ”¹ Placement Group kya hota hai P-Cluster mein?
Soch le tu ek HPC (High Performance Computing) system bana raha hai jahan multiple EC2 instances (jaise compute nodes) mil ke kaam karte hain â€” jaise ek team project mein sab members milke kaam karte hain.
Ab agar ye instances alag-alag jagah pe (data center racks) rakhe ho toh unke beech ka communication slow ho jaata hai.
ğŸ§  Placement Group ek AWS ka feature hai jisse tu instances ko ek hi jagah ya close proximity mein rakh sakta hai â€” taki:
* Network latency kam ho
* Bandwidth zyada ho
* Data transfer fast ho
* Parallel computing smooth ho
ğŸ”¸ Real Life Analogy:
Soch:
* Tu aur tere 4 doston ne ek group project banana hai.
* Agar sab alag-alag cities mein ho, toh Zoom pe kaam karna slow hoga.
* Agar sab ek hi room mein ho, toh sab kuch fast hoga: baat bhi, kaam bhi.
ğŸ‘‰ Yeh hi kaam placement group karta hai â€” sab instances ko ek hi "room" mein rakhta hai, matlab physically ek jaise rack/host pe deploy karta hai.
